## 9. Grading posture — everything IN, nothing written above its grade (no fences)

Will's ruling 2026-06-15: **no fences.** Fencing *omits* — and an omitted result is
one nobody hardens later, lost out in the cold. So **everything goes in**, including
the speculative and the RH-adjacent; the discipline is not exclusion, it is **grading
at true status**. Grading is the *inclusion* mechanism — it keeps a thing on the
record so it *can* be hardened, while never writing it as established before it is.

- **Include the speculative, grade it.** The **Lloyd Exponent** / boundary-rate
  classifier (incl. the zeta `γ≈7/6` observation) is **IN** as a target (FX-T-J,
  CL-T7): the divergence-rate classifier is computed exactly where it can be, graded
  `[MEASURED]`; the **RH connection is recorded and graded `[EMPIRICAL]`/`[INFERENCE]`,
  never written as "Cella supports RH."** Preserved, not lost; safe, by the grade.
- **The spine stays the frontier, graded `[INFERENCE]`.** "Evidence, not confirmation"
  is not omission — the spine is the thing being hardened toward; we simply do not
  write it confirmed before both arms + a separate spine-confirmation land
  (charter-level, Will's). It is on the table, not behind a fence.
- **The one surviving line is honesty, not a fence:** nothing is written MEASURED/
  PROVEN above its true maturity. That is what makes *total inclusion* safe.
- **Dropped per §10:** transplant gate, all IP/patent framing, the "no privileged
  projection" caveat. `K_hol` is available to crown (the cella-as-trunk direction).
  All scope caps lifted — FX-T-G/H/I/J: integer, transcendental, `n>3`, the Floor
  hierarchy, the Lloyd Exponent — every one graded at true maturity.
- The lone genuine exclusion is **Covenant 3** (performance never verdict-bearing) —
  project-wide, permanent, and moot here (we harden a theorem, we do not benchmark).

